    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1888-05-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1888-05-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="494" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d494">
                <head>No. 39.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Sir <persName type="from">L. S.
                                    Sackville West</persName> to Mr. <persName type="to">Bayard</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1888-05-25">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 25, 1888</date>.
                                (Received May 26.)</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: On the 30th of April I had the honor to
                            address you, as instructed by the Marquis of Salisbury, on the subject
                            of the appeals pending in the cases of British vessels seized by the
                            United States in Behring’s Sea, and Her Majesty’s Government have now
                            requested me to ask you for a reply to my above-mentioned
                            communication.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">L. S. Sackville
                            West.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
